 the Anglicized surnames <i>Rees</i> and <i>Rice</i>. Welsh <i>y</i> is a short back vowel /ɪ/. In the medieval period the English approximation of this vowel was either /i/ or /e/, lengthened to /i:/ and /e:/. Subsequent sound changes in English produced the alternative pronunciations represented in <i>Rees</i>, <i>Preece</i> and <i>Rice</i>, <i>Price</i>. The name has also been established in Ireland from an early date.","English: either a topographic name for someone who lived in or near a thicket (Middle English <i>ris</i>, <i>rice</i>, <i>ris</i>, from Old English <i>hrīs</i>, Old Norse <i>hrís</i>), or a habitational name for someone who came from a place called with this word, such as Rise (East Yorkshire).","English: perhaps a nickname from Middle English <i>Rys(e)</i> and <i>Re(e)s</i> which when without a preposition could derive from one or other of several Old French and Middle English words, including Anglo-Norman French <i>ris</i> ‘laughter, smile’, Middle English <i>ris</i>, <i>res</i> ‘stem, stalk’, in origin the same word as in 2 above, and Middle English <i>ris</i>, <i>rise</i>, <i>rice</i>, <i>res</i>, Old French <i>ris</i>, <i>riz</i> ‘rice’, perhaps a nickname for a rice dealer or a cook."],"variants":[{"name":"Reese","meanings":["Welsh: variant of   Rice  .","North German and Dutch (<b>De Reese</b>): nickname for a very big man, from Middle Low German, Middle Dutch <i>rese</i> ‘giant’.","German: habitational name from any of the places called Rees or Reese, in Rhineland and Lower Saxony."]},{"name":"Rees","meanings":["Welsh: variant of   Rice  .","German: habitational name from a place in the Rhineland called Rees.","German: from a short form of the personal name   Andreas  ."]},{"name":"Ryce","meanings":["Variant of   Rice   (German   Reiss  ).","Welsh and English: variant of   Rice  ."]},{"name":"Rise","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Scandinavian Aase, Lief, Sven.","English: variant of   Rice  .","Norwegian: habitational name from any of over twenty farmsteads named Rise, from Old Norse <i>hrís</i> ‘brushwood’. The name also occurs in Sweden and Denmark."]},{"name":"Wrice","meanings":["Probably Welsh or English: variant of   Rice  ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Rice had at least 1 daughter with Margaret Baker."},"et":{"–":"Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1592–1676":"1592–1676","–Male":"Surnud","1676":"1676","1592":"1592","East Grinstead, Sussex, England":"East Grinstead, Sussex, England"},"fi":{"–":"Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1592–1676":"1592–1676","–Male":"Kuollut","1676":"1676","1592":"1592","East Grinstead, Sussex, England":"East Grinstead, Sussex, England"},"fr":{"–":"Décédé","–Female":"Décédée","1592–1676":"1592–1676","–Male":"Décédé","1676":"1676","1592":"1592","East Grinstead, Sussex, England":"East Grinstead, Sussex, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Rice a eu au moins 1 fille avec Margaret Baker."},"de":{"–":"Verstorben","–Female":"Verstorben","1592–1676":"1592–1676","–Male":"Verstorben","1676":"1676","1592":"1592","East Grinstead, Sussex, England":"East Grinstead, Sussex, England","lifeSummary":"Rice hatte mit Margaret Baker mindestens 1 Tochter."},"ht":{"–":"Desede","–Female":"Desede","1592–1676":"1592–1676","–Male":"Desede","1676":"1676","1592":"1592","East Grinstead, Sussex, England":"East Grinstead, Sussex, England"},"hu":{"–":"elhunyt","–Female":"elhunyt","1592–1676":"1592–1676","–Male":"elhunyt","1676":"1676","1592":"1592","East Grinstead, Sussex, England":"East Grinstead, Sussex, England"},"id":{"–":"Telah Meninggal","–Female":"Telah Meninggal","1592–1676":"1592–1676","–Male":"Telah Meninggal","1676":"1676","1592":"1592","East Grinstead, Sussex, England":"East Grinstead, Sussex, England"},"it":{"–":"Deceduto","–Female":"Deceduta","1592–1676":"1592–1676","–Male":"Deceduto","1676":"1676","1592":"1592","East Grinstead, Sussex, England":"East Grinstead, Sussex, England","lifeSummary":"Rice lui avuto almeno 1 figlia con Margaret Baker."},"ja":{"–":"死亡","–Female":"死亡","1592–1676":"1592年–1676年","